descriptionAlternativeDeliveryAddressPri: Code list with codes that are _derived_ from subdivisions. A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces). This means that additional work must be invested in curation of ISO 3166-2 code lists. en_US_saptrc.descriptionAlternativeDeliveryAddressPri: B0kvgwe8GbjV22RT9tTj1w_Code list with codes that are _derived_ from subdivisions. A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces). This means that additional work must be invested in curation of ISO 3166-2 code lists. A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces). This means that additional work must be invested in curation of ISO 3166-2 code lists. So, while formally it the field type is ISO subdivision code, in fact it is a curated subset of ISO 3166-2, prepared for use in postal delivery.

A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces). This means that additional work must be invested in curation of ISO 3166-2 code lists. So, while formally it the field type is ISO subdivision code, in fact it is a curated subset of ISO 3166-2, prepared for use in postal delivery.

eg_de.descriptionAlternativeDeliveryAddressPri: Code list with codes that are _derived_ from subdivisions. A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces). This means that additional work must be invested in curation of ISO 3166-2 code lists. So, while formally it the field type is ISO subdivision code, in fact it is a curated subset of ISO 3166-2, prepared for use in postal delivery.

eg_de.descriptionAlternativeDeliveryAddressTow: City, town, village. A value from a codelist for towns (see ISO 19160-4 definition).
eg_de.descriptionAlternativeDeliveryAddressDis: An addressable area inside of a town (see ISO 19160-4 definition: optional).
eg_de.descriptionAlternativeDeliveryAddressDel: A codelist containing a discriminator to select between address types.
A codelist containing a discriminator to select between address types.

For example, Post Office SouthEast. Needed as the same service identifier is only unique within the scope of the qualifier (that is, the same identifier could be used in different post offices in the same town).

A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces). This means that additional work must be invested in curation of ISO 3166-2 code lists. So, while formally it the field type is ISO subdivision code, in fact it is a curated subset of ISO 3166-2, prepared for use in postal delivery.

A region for postal must provide a disjoint cut, in ISO 3166-2 it is not always the case (for example, France 14 provinces, 95 departments, departments intersect with provinces).
